Alerts from an organizationâ€™s Security Center provide critical information 
concerning potential security threats and incidents to an organization.
    
By receiving these alerts, an organization can quickly identify incidents and take 
appropriate action to respond to and mitigate the threat. 
  
Assume we are working with three relations:
-- alerts (the primary table): Contains operational data about actual events detected by the system.
-- users: Holds info. about the people in the organization that are generating the alerts.
-- policies: Defines the organizational rules that were violated by the users.
